WEBVTT

00:00:06.694 --> 00:00:07.612
Come on, Taiga!

00:00:07.695 --> 00:00:09.531
Don't fall behind!

00:00:11.616 --> 00:00:13.660
Keep up or you'll lose!

00:00:17.956 --> 00:00:20.458
Even if our ace runner buys us time,
there's no point

00:00:20.959 --> 00:00:23.044
if everyone else wastes it.

00:00:24.838 --> 00:00:25.755
Taiga.

00:00:27.882 --> 00:00:29.300
You're off the team.

00:00:33.263 --> 00:00:36.307
- Man, that's brutal.
- Poor guy.

00:00:36.391 --> 00:00:37.851
He didn't make it after all.

00:02:01.851 --> 00:02:03.895
‪TANOMI

00:02:03.978 --> 00:02:06.231
So you're going
to tour properties together?

00:02:07.857 --> 00:02:10.985
Yeah. We're going on our next day off.

00:02:13.029 --> 00:02:14.614
You don't waste any time, huh?

00:02:14.697 --> 00:02:16.324
It's not what you're thinking.

00:02:16.407 --> 00:02:19.827
I'm only going for moral support.

00:02:19.911 --> 00:02:21.829
Are you stupid?

00:02:21.913 --> 00:02:24.999
You think she'd tour properties with a guy
who's not her parent or boyfriend?

00:02:30.046 --> 00:02:30.964
You think so?

00:02:31.047 --> 00:02:32.632
- Shige.
- Huh?

00:02:32.715 --> 00:02:34.634
Taiga is about to get a girlfriend.

00:02:34.717 --> 00:02:37.512
- Noa! It's not like that!
- I didn't expect that.

00:02:37.595 --> 00:02:39.013
Like I said, it's not like that.

00:02:40.348 --> 00:02:42.809
And plus, even if it was,

00:02:42.892 --> 00:02:44.686
our relationship wouldn't go anywhere.

00:02:45.436 --> 00:02:46.437
Why?

00:02:47.772 --> 00:02:49.899
She's an international student from Korea,

00:02:50.483 --> 00:02:52.568
so she shouldn't be with someone like me.

00:02:53.111 --> 00:02:54.570
Someone like you?

00:02:54.654 --> 00:02:56.030
I mean…

00:02:56.614 --> 00:02:58.950
Someone with no future.

00:03:01.619 --> 00:03:02.954
So you're saying

00:03:03.037 --> 00:03:06.040
that a restaurant employee
is going to accompany you?

00:03:08.876 --> 00:03:12.255
Yes, um…

00:03:12.922 --> 00:03:14.924
Kind of like a Japanese advisor.

00:03:17.135 --> 00:03:19.804
Taiga isn't suspicious at all.

00:03:19.887 --> 00:03:22.515
He came with me
out of the kindness of his heart.

00:03:22.598 --> 00:03:23.433
‪KAEDE REAL ESTATE

00:03:23.516 --> 00:03:24.642
All right.

00:03:24.726 --> 00:03:28.855
Well then, let me suggest some
properties that might fit your taste.

00:03:28.938 --> 00:03:30.356
Thank you.

00:03:30.940 --> 00:03:34.902
I picked out a few
that fit your requirements.

00:03:34.986 --> 00:03:35.945
In your case,

00:03:36.029 --> 00:03:40.742
the trickiest part
is that you have to move out in one year.

00:03:41.576 --> 00:03:44.620
Well, why don't we take
a tour of them first?

00:03:50.543 --> 00:03:51.419
Well…

00:03:52.754 --> 00:03:54.881
You're leaving in a year, huh?

00:03:55.381 --> 00:03:56.466
Yes.

00:03:56.549 --> 00:03:58.926
If I can actually graduate, that is.

00:04:00.553 --> 00:04:02.722
My student visa is going to expire,

00:04:02.805 --> 00:04:06.851
so I can't stay in Japan
unless I start working.

00:04:07.352 --> 00:04:08.519
Oh, your visa?

00:04:09.270 --> 00:04:11.314
Wow, that's amazing.

00:04:12.815 --> 00:04:13.900
Amazing?

00:04:14.484 --> 00:04:16.194
What about it is amazing?

00:04:18.363 --> 00:04:21.366
Well, just talking about visas and stuff

00:04:21.449 --> 00:04:23.576
is amazing from my point of view.

00:04:24.869 --> 00:04:27.246
It's like you're talking about
a whole different world.

00:04:27.830 --> 00:04:29.791
There's nothing amazing about it.

00:04:30.416 --> 00:04:33.169
International students
all stay here with student visas,

00:04:33.252 --> 00:04:35.463
and go back to Korea once they graduate.

00:04:35.963 --> 00:04:37.465
I see…

00:04:38.091 --> 00:04:39.550
Of course…

00:04:39.634 --> 00:04:41.177
Before that,

00:04:41.260 --> 00:04:44.180
I hope I can cross things
off my bucket list.

00:04:45.598 --> 00:04:46.974
Bucket list?

00:04:48.643 --> 00:04:49.477
Yes.

00:04:50.186 --> 00:04:54.732
A list of things that I want to do
before I die.

00:04:54.816 --> 00:04:57.777
One item on my bucket list

00:04:57.860 --> 00:05:00.863
is to try every kind
of Japanese convenience store snack.

00:05:01.989 --> 00:05:02.990
I see.

00:05:03.741 --> 00:05:05.034
Interesting.

00:05:05.118 --> 00:05:08.246
Why don't you make one too?

00:05:08.329 --> 00:05:09.330
What?

00:05:10.456 --> 00:05:12.458
I don't think that's necessary.

00:05:12.542 --> 00:05:14.210
You agree, right Noa?

00:05:14.293 --> 00:05:16.629
But your daughter
is in middle school, right?

00:05:17.964 --> 00:05:19.924
Then I guess she'd want a new device.

00:05:20.007 --> 00:05:22.468
As long as I can make a call,
that's enough for me.

00:05:22.552 --> 00:05:24.512
They're all the same, no?

00:05:24.595 --> 00:05:26.764
They are not all the same.

00:05:26.848 --> 00:05:28.683
The image quality and stuff are different.

00:05:28.766 --> 00:05:30.101
You think so?

00:05:31.436 --> 00:05:35.106
So your labor right now is going to turn
into your daughter's smartphone?

00:05:35.189 --> 00:05:37.817
That's right. It's ridiculous.

00:05:37.900 --> 00:05:41.612
I wish she'd just keep using
the one she's used to.

00:05:55.543 --> 00:05:58.629
I don't know… It's pretty nice but…

00:05:58.713 --> 00:06:00.089
What do you think?

00:06:05.887 --> 00:06:07.555
- Excuse me.
- Yes?

00:06:07.638 --> 00:06:11.976
Does a lot of smoke rise up
from the restaurants below?

00:06:14.145 --> 00:06:16.898
I don't think it'll be a problem,

00:06:17.481 --> 00:06:19.066
but I can ask about it.

00:06:19.150 --> 00:06:20.193
Okay, thank you.

00:06:22.945 --> 00:06:25.198
The placement of the exhaust fans
might be an issue.

00:06:27.200 --> 00:06:28.784
I didn't notice that at all.

00:06:37.084 --> 00:06:37.919
Oh, Taiga.

00:06:39.462 --> 00:06:41.964
- Can I ask you something?
- Yes.

00:06:42.048 --> 00:06:45.760
This room doesn't have a refrigerator
or washing machine or anything.

00:06:47.094 --> 00:06:49.931
Rooms in Korea usually come
with appliances.

00:06:50.014 --> 00:06:51.390
Oh really?

00:06:52.808 --> 00:06:54.644
Well, it's not like
anything is wrong here.

00:06:54.727 --> 00:06:57.438
In Japan, this is normal.

00:06:58.189 --> 00:06:59.232
Oh, good.

00:06:59.315 --> 00:07:02.777
If you have any questions,
don't hesitate to ask me.

00:07:03.945 --> 00:07:05.446
Thank you.

00:07:10.618 --> 00:07:12.036
These windows are cute!

00:07:15.081 --> 00:07:16.749
The kitchen is big too.

00:07:19.168 --> 00:07:20.503
I like this place.

00:07:22.922 --> 00:07:24.882
This is a really nice place.

00:07:25.424 --> 00:07:29.220
I agree. The rent is not too high either.

00:07:29.303 --> 00:07:31.138
I like it a lot.

00:07:31.639 --> 00:07:33.849
I think my mind is set on this one.

00:07:34.976 --> 00:07:36.519
Wait a second.

00:07:50.283 --> 00:07:51.826
No issues with the security either.

00:07:59.125 --> 00:08:01.127
Thank you for today.

00:08:01.210 --> 00:08:03.671
I found a nice place thanks to you.

00:08:03.754 --> 00:08:05.548
I didn't do anything.

00:08:06.215 --> 00:08:08.009
I'm glad you found a place.

00:08:09.594 --> 00:08:13.222
I hope they accept my application.

00:08:15.391 --> 00:08:18.060
It'll be fine. I'm sure.

00:08:25.067 --> 00:08:26.277
Taiga.

00:08:28.029 --> 00:08:29.780
Today, I…

00:08:31.532 --> 00:08:33.117
had a lot of fun.

00:08:36.537 --> 00:08:39.206
Looking at houses is fun, isn't it?

00:08:44.045 --> 00:08:45.338
Um…

00:08:47.006 --> 00:08:51.719
{\an8}STRAWBERRY CARAMEL

00:08:57.516 --> 00:09:00.561
This is a thank you gift for today.

00:09:00.645 --> 00:09:01.729
Here you go.

00:09:09.445 --> 00:09:10.988
Thank you.

00:09:16.952 --> 00:09:18.204
Well, see you…

00:09:19.705 --> 00:09:20.748
Right…

00:09:22.833 --> 00:09:25.711
Well then… See you.

00:09:57.952 --> 00:10:00.788
You should give up on Onigiri Man.

00:10:00.871 --> 00:10:03.040
We had a good vibe,

00:10:03.124 --> 00:10:04.875
so why didn't he ask me out
on another date?

00:10:06.210 --> 00:10:07.753
Did I do something wrong?

00:10:08.421 --> 00:10:09.672
That's not it.

00:10:09.755 --> 00:10:11.966
Didn't I tell you before?

00:10:12.967 --> 00:10:14.844
Japanese men are extremely reserved

00:10:14.927 --> 00:10:18.472
when it comes to expressing
their feelings.

00:10:18.556 --> 00:10:20.683
Isn't that just your opinion?

00:10:21.183 --> 00:10:22.768
Park Rin!

00:10:22.852 --> 00:10:25.229
How many times do I have to tell you?

00:10:25.855 --> 00:10:28.858
I am a professional content buyer, okay?

00:10:28.941 --> 00:10:33.738
I've watched
all the movies and dramas to death.

00:10:33.821 --> 00:10:35.406
But dramas are just dramas.

00:10:35.489 --> 00:10:36.323
What are you saying!

00:10:36.407 --> 00:10:41.704
Dramas reflect
the culture of that country.

00:10:41.787 --> 00:10:43.622
According to my database,

00:10:43.706 --> 00:10:47.752
main characters in Japanese dramas
are more sensitive.

00:10:47.835 --> 00:10:52.798
In many stories, they overthink everything
and don't even get together in the end.

00:10:54.175 --> 00:10:55.134
Really?

00:10:56.135 --> 00:10:57.303
Yes.

00:10:59.096 --> 00:11:03.559
Dating someone of a different nationality
isn't easy.

00:11:03.642 --> 00:11:05.519
So don't try to rush into it
unnecessarily.

00:11:08.439 --> 00:11:09.607
Yeah?

00:11:10.191 --> 00:11:11.734
Park Rin.

00:11:11.817 --> 00:11:13.486
If you keep acting like that,

00:11:13.569 --> 00:11:16.030
- I will tell your mother.
- Don't you dare!

00:11:17.406 --> 00:11:20.117
Fine. I'll stop.

00:11:21.535 --> 00:11:24.580
I'm here to study, after all.

00:11:24.663 --> 00:11:26.123
That's right.

00:11:27.917 --> 00:11:29.710
I have to go. Bye!

00:11:30.419 --> 00:11:31.837
Enjoy the party.

00:11:34.215 --> 00:11:36.759
- How has your mother been lately?
- Who knows?

00:11:37.718 --> 00:11:40.346
I'm sure she's having fun with a guy,
as usual.

00:11:40.429 --> 00:11:42.389
It's okay, I'll do it myself.

00:11:43.599 --> 00:11:45.518
She'll show up when she feels like it.

00:11:47.019 --> 00:11:48.270
You're okay with that?

00:11:50.397 --> 00:11:52.900
I don't have any other choice, do I?

00:11:54.026 --> 00:11:55.236
More importantly,

00:11:56.320 --> 00:11:57.905
are you serious about what you said?

00:11:58.781 --> 00:12:02.159
Well, ever since I started,
I've been preparing myself

00:12:03.786 --> 00:12:06.413
for the possibility of closing
the restaurant when I retire.

00:12:09.583 --> 00:12:12.545
Hey, if you're going to retire,

00:12:13.462 --> 00:12:14.922
why not have Taiga take over?

00:12:15.881 --> 00:12:18.300
That would be a lot to ask of him.

00:12:18.884 --> 00:12:19.718
You think so?

00:12:27.226 --> 00:12:29.645
I didn't pass the contest again.

00:12:30.354 --> 00:12:31.522
What about you?

00:12:31.605 --> 00:12:33.440
I didn't make it either.

00:12:39.446 --> 00:12:40.281
I heard Amane

00:12:40.864 --> 00:12:43.284
is going to have her solo exhibition
in New York.

00:12:43.784 --> 00:12:44.868
She's making figurines too.

00:12:46.829 --> 00:12:47.871
Wow.

00:12:47.955 --> 00:12:50.332
When you have that much talent,

00:12:50.416 --> 00:12:52.084
I bet you don't
have to worry about your future.

00:12:52.167 --> 00:12:55.379
After graduating, she can just go
straight into the professional world.

00:12:57.131 --> 00:12:59.466
I have to decide on what to do myself.

00:13:00.134 --> 00:13:04.138
Rin, you're going back to Korea
and not finding a job over here, right?

00:13:04.930 --> 00:13:08.642
For the most part, that's my plan…

00:13:09.184 --> 00:13:10.811
I'm so jealous.

00:13:10.894 --> 00:13:13.814
Maybe I'll follow you and go to Korea too?

00:13:13.897 --> 00:13:15.024
Just kidding.

00:13:33.459 --> 00:13:34.501
Thank you for the food.

00:13:43.927 --> 00:13:44.803
That's delicious.

00:13:47.640 --> 00:13:49.224
What is this dish called?

00:13:49.808 --> 00:13:52.811
Today, it's Pacific Barrelfish
cooked in a bamboo steamer.

00:13:53.646 --> 00:13:55.856
It's a white fish,
but it's nice and fatty, right?

00:13:55.939 --> 00:13:59.526
When it's freshly caught,
the skin is greasy.

00:13:59.610 --> 00:14:00.903
Greasy?

00:14:01.987 --> 00:14:05.240
Is that different from "slimy"?

00:14:05.949 --> 00:14:07.910
Well, it's basically in the same family.

00:14:07.993 --> 00:14:11.038
You're so knowledgeable.
You're amazing, Master.

00:14:11.121 --> 00:14:14.333
A cook should be knowledgeable
about his ingredients.

00:14:14.958 --> 00:14:18.504
Even when I go to an aquarium,
I know almost all the fish there.

00:14:18.587 --> 00:14:20.047
Really? Wow.

00:14:21.966 --> 00:14:25.219
That reminds me…
I haven't been to an aquarium in ages.

00:14:25.302 --> 00:14:26.470
Oh really?

00:14:27.721 --> 00:14:29.306
You should have someone take you.

00:14:33.852 --> 00:14:35.187
Hey.

00:14:35.270 --> 00:14:37.231
If you want to, just ask her.

00:14:38.065 --> 00:14:39.525
What are you talking about?

00:14:39.608 --> 00:14:42.403
You've been staring at her the whole time.

00:14:43.028 --> 00:14:46.323
- I was not staring.
- You were staring at her like a creep.

00:14:46.865 --> 00:14:48.492
You were eavesdropping too, right?

00:14:49.535 --> 00:14:51.495
Hurry up and take this chance.

00:14:53.664 --> 00:14:57.501
But she said she's going back
to Korea in a year.

00:14:57.584 --> 00:15:00.004
Even if I ask her to go with me,
it'll only trouble her.

00:15:00.087 --> 00:15:01.797
Yeah, yeah… Just go!

00:15:08.053 --> 00:15:09.096
Um…

00:15:10.014 --> 00:15:10.973
Yes?

00:15:11.724 --> 00:15:16.186
I overheard
that you haven't been to an aquarium.

00:15:16.812 --> 00:15:17.896
Yes.

00:15:17.980 --> 00:15:20.149
I haven't been to one since I was a child.

00:15:23.402 --> 00:15:24.611
If you…

00:15:26.447 --> 00:15:29.700
happen to have a day
where you have absolutely nothing to do,

00:15:30.409 --> 00:15:33.370
- would you like to go to an aquarium--
- Yes.

00:15:34.788 --> 00:15:36.665
Huh? Really?

00:15:37.624 --> 00:15:38.917
I'd love to go.

00:15:39.543 --> 00:15:40.711
Let's go together.

