00:20:28.623 --> 00:20:30.000
{\an8}They're not here, huh?

00:20:30.584 --> 00:20:31.626
{\an8}Are they on break?

00:20:38.383 --> 00:20:40.469
There's a sea lion show. Want to see that?

00:20:40.552 --> 00:20:42.471
Sea lions are really smart and cute.

00:20:42.554 --> 00:20:44.931
Yeah. I'm excited.

00:20:45.807 --> 00:20:47.351
- It's this way.
- Okay.

00:20:49.895 --> 00:20:52.731
How do you say sea lion in Korean?

00:20:53.482 --> 00:20:54.691
Mulgae.

00:20:54.775 --> 00:20:55.901
Mulgae?

00:20:55.984 --> 00:20:57.736
- We will make an announcement soon.
- Mulgae.

00:20:58.779 --> 00:21:00.072
We're very sorry.

00:21:01.114 --> 00:21:03.283
We apologize.

00:21:03.367 --> 00:21:04.451
Excuse me.

00:21:04.534 --> 00:21:07.079
We're sorry, but there were some
issues with the tank.

00:21:07.162 --> 00:21:08.872
So we're trying to repair it now.

00:21:08.955 --> 00:21:10.749
What? Oh no…

00:21:10.832 --> 00:21:12.000
We're terribly sorry.

00:21:12.084 --> 00:21:13.668
What should we do?

00:21:15.796 --> 00:21:19.174
This aquarium is famous
for their special drink. Want to try it?

00:21:19.257 --> 00:21:22.219
- Sounds good.
- It's this way.

00:21:24.262 --> 00:21:25.263
{\an8}PENGUIN SODA

00:21:25.347 --> 00:21:26.807
{\an8}How cute!

00:21:26.890 --> 00:21:30.894
I'm sorry. We just ran out
of the Penguin Soda.

00:21:30.977 --> 00:21:34.481
You've got to be kidding.
We came here expecting to buy this.

00:21:34.564 --> 00:21:36.066
You think it's some joke?

00:21:36.149 --> 00:21:38.318
You didn't even do the sea lion show.

00:21:39.236 --> 00:21:41.947
I can't believe we had to pay
the same entrance fee.

00:21:42.572 --> 00:21:43.949
- Let's go.
- Yeah.

00:21:44.825 --> 00:21:46.368
I'm very sorry.

00:21:47.119 --> 00:21:49.079
Hello, can you take our order?

00:21:49.579 --> 00:21:52.374
I'm sorry,
we're out of our special Penguin Soda.

00:21:52.457 --> 00:21:55.293
No worries. Must be tough, huh?

00:22:11.226 --> 00:22:12.436
I'm sorry.

00:22:13.019 --> 00:22:15.313
It's not going as planned at all.

00:22:15.814 --> 00:22:16.648
No…

00:22:17.315 --> 00:22:20.902
I appreciate how much thought
you put into it.

00:22:26.199 --> 00:22:27.409
The sea lion show…

00:22:27.909 --> 00:22:29.578
I hope it reopens soon.

00:22:33.331 --> 00:22:35.959
BIG BRO

00:22:41.339 --> 00:22:43.508
- Give me a second.
- Take your time.

00:22:48.513 --> 00:22:51.266
Sorry, I was kind of busy.

00:22:52.225 --> 00:22:53.518
What's wrong?

00:22:54.394 --> 00:22:58.064
Mom fell at home and hurt herself.

00:22:58.732 --> 00:22:59.900
What?

00:22:59.983 --> 00:23:01.193
Is she all right?

00:23:01.276 --> 00:23:04.112
Yeah, they're taking
a look at her at the hospital.

00:23:04.196 --> 00:23:05.739
It wasn't anything serious.

00:23:06.865 --> 00:23:08.575
Thank goodness.

00:23:09.951 --> 00:23:11.620
You know,

00:23:12.370 --> 00:23:14.456
why aren't you looking after the family?

00:23:14.539 --> 00:23:16.082
Why do I have to take time off work?

00:23:18.084 --> 00:23:19.169
Sorry…

00:23:21.213 --> 00:23:23.840
Whatever… We'll take care of it.

00:23:27.010 --> 00:23:28.553
Thank you.

00:23:30.347 --> 00:23:33.475
You're not young anymore,
so enough of this "self-discovery" stuff.

00:23:33.975 --> 00:23:35.018
Bye.

00:23:42.234 --> 00:23:45.153
An announcement to all guests.

00:23:45.237 --> 00:23:47.280
We are terribly sorry,

00:23:47.364 --> 00:23:50.492
but today's sea lion show
will be canceled.

00:23:52.118 --> 00:23:55.038
An announcement to all guests.

00:23:55.121 --> 00:23:57.332
We are terribly sorry,

00:23:57.415 --> 00:24:00.585
but today's sea lion show
will be canceled.

00:24:08.093 --> 00:24:11.179
I wish I could've seen
the sea lions with you.

00:24:11.763 --> 00:24:13.014
Too bad.

00:24:16.559 --> 00:24:17.894
I'm sorry.

00:24:19.062 --> 00:24:21.940
This aquarium was supposed to be more fun.

00:24:22.691 --> 00:24:24.901
It's not your fault, Taiga.

00:24:26.319 --> 00:24:27.529
Well,

00:24:28.446 --> 00:24:30.240
I'm used to this, anyway.

00:24:31.324 --> 00:24:33.201
Used to what?

00:24:35.996 --> 00:24:40.333
Things not going according to plan.

00:24:42.961 --> 00:24:46.131
It's true that we've been
out of luck this whole day.

00:24:46.840 --> 00:24:51.344
But halfway through, I started to wonder,
"What's going to happen next?"

00:24:51.928 --> 00:24:53.763
And that was actually exciting.

00:24:55.974 --> 00:24:58.476
It's not that I don't have a plan.

00:24:59.227 --> 00:25:02.605
I just can't seem
to follow through with it.

00:25:07.193 --> 00:25:11.781
Nothing in my life
has ever gone according to plan.

00:25:17.454 --> 00:25:19.164
Compared to that,

00:25:20.415 --> 00:25:21.750
you are amazing, Rin.

00:25:22.542 --> 00:25:24.294
Why is that?

00:25:24.377 --> 00:25:26.588
You came to a foreign country on your own,

00:25:27.130 --> 00:25:30.592
and you're moving forward
toward your dream.

00:25:30.675 --> 00:25:33.511
You have the ability to take action,

00:25:34.095 --> 00:25:35.430
and you have courage.

00:25:38.016 --> 00:25:41.561
Did you try making a bucket list?

00:25:42.771 --> 00:25:43.688
What?

00:25:45.732 --> 00:25:47.609
I don't have any dreams or anything.

00:25:48.485 --> 00:25:51.613
It doesn't have to be
something serious like that.

00:25:52.322 --> 00:25:57.077
Bucket lists can also help you find goals.

00:25:58.203 --> 00:26:00.080
The truth is,

00:26:00.163 --> 00:26:02.374
I set up a goal for myself today.

00:26:04.501 --> 00:26:06.795
Since you always cook for me,

00:26:07.295 --> 00:26:09.506
I wanted to cook for you today.

00:26:11.091 --> 00:26:13.635
But it was really hard.

00:26:15.261 --> 00:26:16.471
Take a look.

00:26:21.267 --> 00:26:24.145
Wow. They're huge.

00:26:24.229 --> 00:26:26.981
I thought that might make you happier.

00:26:29.776 --> 00:26:32.153
I'm still working on it.

00:26:36.658 --> 00:26:38.868
But I did my best.

00:26:53.800 --> 00:26:55.468
- Thank you.
- Enjoy.

00:27:09.023 --> 00:27:11.317
- It's good.
- Really?

00:27:13.611 --> 00:27:14.654
Yes.

00:27:15.530 --> 00:27:16.739
I'm glad.

00:27:20.368 --> 00:27:21.411
It's good.

00:27:24.539 --> 00:27:26.374
It's really good.

00:27:27.000 --> 00:27:28.376
Thank you.

00:27:35.884 --> 00:27:40.638
Thank you very much for visiting today.

00:27:41.264 --> 00:27:43.725
We will be closing soon.

00:27:44.309 --> 00:27:45.435
We look forward to…

00:27:48.438 --> 00:27:51.274
Taiga! We don't have to go out of our way!

00:27:51.357 --> 00:27:53.985
No! We should see the rays.

00:27:54.068 --> 00:27:56.029
They're in the biggest tank.

00:27:57.405 --> 00:27:59.073
We're almost there.

00:27:59.574 --> 00:28:00.408
‪CREATURES OF OARAI

00:28:02.535 --> 00:28:04.996
Excuse me. Can we go inside?

00:28:05.079 --> 00:28:07.081
Sorry, we closed it off.

00:28:07.165 --> 00:28:09.709
Please, let us in!

00:28:09.792 --> 00:28:12.378
Rules are rules. Sorry.

00:28:12.462 --> 00:28:15.673
Is there no way?
I really want her to see the rays.

00:28:15.757 --> 00:28:17.675
We'll leave as soon as we see them.

00:28:17.759 --> 00:28:21.471
Once we let a guest in,
the employees have to stay behind.

00:28:22.805 --> 00:28:24.516
Right…

00:28:26.309 --> 00:28:27.769
Sorry for troubling you.

00:28:27.852 --> 00:28:29.145
Sorry about that.

00:28:29.938 --> 00:28:32.023
Okay, good bye.

00:28:35.193 --> 00:28:36.110
Wait, Sir.

00:28:39.113 --> 00:28:42.325
I'll go patrol the other areas,
so during that time,

00:28:42.408 --> 00:28:43.618
you can go inside.

00:28:45.954 --> 00:28:47.622
Thank you!

00:28:48.915 --> 00:28:50.041
There it is!

00:28:50.124 --> 00:28:51.626
Gaoli. Ray.

00:28:52.752 --> 00:28:54.337
How cute!

00:28:56.965 --> 00:29:00.051
I'm so glad you got to see it.

00:29:05.765 --> 00:29:07.350
Wow…

00:29:08.434 --> 00:29:10.144
We have this place all to ourselves.

00:29:13.606 --> 00:29:15.483
We do.

00:29:44.220 --> 00:29:45.179
- Taiga.
- Hey…

00:29:47.640 --> 00:29:51.144
There is something I want to tell you.

00:29:54.522 --> 00:29:55.690
Yes?

00:30:04.741 --> 00:30:06.117
- Taiga, I--
- Today,

00:30:08.995 --> 00:30:11.581
this date didn't go as planned at all,

00:30:12.749 --> 00:30:16.753
and I felt like more and more
of a failure.

00:30:19.172 --> 00:30:22.884
But when I'm with you,

00:30:24.594 --> 00:30:27.889
I feel a weight off my shoulders.

00:30:29.974 --> 00:30:33.645
I feel like I can move forward.

00:30:47.325 --> 00:30:48.409
I…

00:30:50.703 --> 00:30:52.288
like you,

00:30:54.332 --> 00:30:55.541
Rin.

00:31:03.800 --> 00:31:07.053
Will you please go out with me?

00:31:11.849 --> 00:31:12.809
Yes.

00:31:34.747 --> 00:31:36.249
Oh, that reminds me.

00:31:36.958 --> 00:31:39.168
I'll give this back to you.

00:31:41.754 --> 00:31:42.714
Thank you.

00:31:43.715 --> 00:31:46.009
But why now?

00:31:46.551 --> 00:31:50.888
Because now I don't need an excuse
to see you anymore.

00:31:54.308 --> 00:31:55.226
Thank you.

00:32:09.949 --> 00:32:12.410
I can't believe we're dating!

00:32:13.745 --> 00:32:15.872
Oh my god! What do I do?

00:32:25.423 --> 00:32:29.886
JUN-HO! BIG NEWS!

00:32:29.969 --> 00:32:33.765
‪TANOMI

00:32:34.474 --> 00:32:36.059
You'll definitely love this place.

00:32:36.142 --> 00:32:37.351
Really?

00:32:37.435 --> 00:32:38.352
I can't wait.

00:32:41.105 --> 00:32:43.941
I'll leave it up to you.
When you're done, I'll taste it.

00:32:44.025 --> 00:32:46.110
Okay. Thank you.

00:32:48.321 --> 00:32:50.782
- Good evening.
- Welcome.

00:32:50.865 --> 00:32:52.575
You came?

00:32:52.658 --> 00:32:55.953
Taiga, sorry for interrupting your work.
Do you have a second?

00:32:56.037 --> 00:32:57.580
Yes, he does.

00:32:59.874 --> 00:33:00.708
You do.

00:33:06.464 --> 00:33:07.298
Jun-ho.

00:33:14.972 --> 00:33:18.059
Hello. I'm Kang Jun-ho, Rin's senior.

00:33:18.142 --> 00:33:19.560
Nice to meet you.

00:33:22.980 --> 00:33:24.023
Jun-ho?

00:33:25.149 --> 00:33:26.651
Nice to meet you.

00:33:27.235 --> 00:33:28.861
I'm Hase Taiga.

00:33:29.862 --> 00:33:32.532
He's been helping me since
I was going to college in Korea,

00:33:32.615 --> 00:33:34.367
so we've known each other for a long time.

00:33:34.450 --> 00:33:37.745
I confide in him a lot.
He's like a dependable older brother.

00:33:38.329 --> 00:33:40.581
Oh, really? From college?

00:33:42.667 --> 00:33:44.085
And this is…

00:33:46.587 --> 00:33:49.006
my boyfriend, Taiga.

00:33:56.055 --> 00:33:57.098
He looks nice.

00:33:57.181 --> 00:33:58.349
Right?

00:33:58.432 --> 00:33:59.934
He's a really good cook too.

00:34:00.601 --> 00:34:03.146
Let's have drinks together,

00:34:03.229 --> 00:34:05.439
and eat Taiga's cooking today.

00:34:09.777 --> 00:34:12.196
Rin, I'm sorry.

00:34:12.947 --> 00:34:16.325
There's an emergency
and I have to go back to work.

00:34:16.409 --> 00:34:18.119
But you said you finished work…

00:34:18.202 --> 00:34:21.038
There was some kind of trouble
and they need me in a hurry.

00:34:21.956 --> 00:34:22.790
I'm really sorry.

00:34:24.417 --> 00:34:26.210
He said he needs to rush back to work.

00:34:26.294 --> 00:34:27.128
What?

00:34:27.211 --> 00:34:29.422
I wanted to formally
introduce you guys, but…

00:34:29.505 --> 00:34:30.339
I'll go now.

00:34:40.558 --> 00:34:41.601
Bye.

00:35:01.370 --> 00:35:02.246
That's hot!

00:35:09.462 --> 00:35:11.172
What's wrong?

00:35:11.255 --> 00:35:13.925
Were you dumped by a girl or something?

00:35:14.800 --> 00:35:18.221
Yes. Is it that obvious?

00:35:18.304 --> 00:35:20.514
Wow, I was right.

00:35:20.598 --> 00:35:24.060
What? Why were you dumped?
You're so good looking.

00:35:24.143 --> 00:35:25.686
Did she have a man already?

00:35:30.274 --> 00:35:34.028
You just have to steal her away.

00:35:34.111 --> 00:35:35.696
I can't do that.

00:35:36.697 --> 00:35:38.532
That would make me the worst type of man…

00:35:43.329 --> 00:35:45.998
It's okay! It's okay!

00:35:46.082 --> 00:35:47.959
{\an8}That was delicious.

00:35:48.042 --> 00:35:50.211
{\an8}Your cooking is the best.

00:35:50.294 --> 00:35:51.212
{\an8}Thank you.

00:35:51.295 --> 00:35:53.673
{\an8}You really surprised me today, though.

00:35:54.382 --> 00:35:57.385
{\an8}I didn't think you would
bring Jun-ho out of the blue.

00:35:58.010 --> 00:35:59.262
{\an8}What?

00:35:59.345 --> 00:36:03.432
{\an8}I thought it was normal
to introduce my boyfriend to my friend.

00:36:04.016 --> 00:36:05.184
{\an8}Was that weird?

00:36:05.268 --> 00:36:07.019
{\an8}Not at all.

00:36:07.645 --> 00:36:11.023
{\an8}I'm happy you introduced me
to your senior.

00:36:11.565 --> 00:36:12.525
{\an8}Okay, good.

00:36:13.693 --> 00:36:14.944
{\an8}From now on,

00:36:15.569 --> 00:36:19.824
{\an8}let's tell each other whenever something
doesn't feel right.

00:36:22.368 --> 00:36:23.244
{\an8}Of course.

00:36:24.328 --> 00:36:26.956
{\an8}- I promise.
- Don't forget it.

00:36:45.308 --> 00:36:46.309
{\an8}There.

00:36:52.857 --> 00:36:54.567
The bucket list thing…

00:36:55.860 --> 00:36:57.611
I'm thinking of doing it too.

00:36:58.404 --> 00:36:59.530
What?

00:36:59.613 --> 00:37:01.449
You found a goal?

00:37:40.112 --> 00:37:41.155
This.

00:37:51.957 --> 00:37:55.127
That's not what a bucket list is.

00:37:56.253 --> 00:37:57.505
Really?

00:38:02.510 --> 00:38:05.346
A kiss isn't a life goal, is it?

00:38:06.389 --> 00:38:07.223
That's true.

00:38:07.807 --> 00:38:09.100
You're so funny.

00:38:09.767 --> 00:38:11.352
That's embarrassing.

00:38:12.353 --> 00:38:14.730
Yeah, it's embarrassing.

00:38:17.483 --> 00:38:18.609
But it made me happy.

00:38:25.074 --> 00:38:26.367
How embarrassing.

00:38:29.203 --> 00:38:30.830
{\an8}Are you embarrassed?

00:38:30.913 --> 00:38:31.956
{\an8}So cute.

00:38:33.124 --> 00:38:34.291
Whatever.

00:38:34.875 --> 00:38:36.544
Communication issues, huh?

00:38:36.627 --> 00:38:38.003
PREVIEW

00:38:38.087 --> 00:38:40.047
{\an8}Maybe it is difficult for two people

00:38:40.131 --> 00:38:42.133
{\an8}from different backgrounds to be together?

